{{wikipedia}}
==English==

===Etymology===
A combination of the surname of its inventor [[w:Adolphe Sax|Adolphe Sax]] (1814–1894) + a connecting 'o' to make the word pronounceable + the English affix "[[phone]]", from Greek [[φωνή]] (''fōnḗ'', 'voice').

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{musici}} A [[single reed instrument]] musical instrument of the [[woodwind]] family, usually made of [[brass]] and with a distinctive loop bringing the bell upwards

====Derived terms====
*[[saxophonist]]
*[[alto saxophone]]

